ncial flows that continue to plague the world economy. Drawing on this theory, Gallagher outlines the significant opportunities and obstacles to regulating cross-border finance in the twenty-first century.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aGeneral Economics. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  adeveloping economy, global financial crisis, financial flows, BRICS coalition, global economic governance institutions, econometric analysis, monetary power, international political economy.2 aKnowledge Unlatchedefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060674440uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9780801454615?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780801454615423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780801454615/original  a978-3-11-060674-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles